data.name: labelDescription.Text
data.value:
Mockingbird is an application developed by programmers to facilitate the writing of unit tests. The application is designed to automate the mocking of files and offers two primary functionalities :
1. Mocking a Single File : Users can select an individual file, and the application will mock only that specific file. 2. Mocking All Dependencies : Users can choose a root folder, and the application will analyze all.c and .h files within that folder to gather all included dependencies.
By streamlining the process of mocking files and their dependencies, Mockingbird significantly reduces the time and effort required for unit testing, enabling developers to focus more on writing and improving their code.
